{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting MapLibre iOS 6.10.0, using "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.protomaps.com\/pmtiles\/"},{"type":"text","text":" as a data source is supported. You can prefix your vector tile source with "},{"code":"pmtiles:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load a PMTiles file. The rest of the URL continue with be ","type":"text"},{"code":"https:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load a remote PMTiles file, ","type":"text"},{"code":"asset:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load an asset or ","type":"text"},{"code":"file:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load a local PMTiles file.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"PMTiles sources currently do not support caching or offline pack downloads.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Oliver Wipfli has made a style available that combines a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" basemap togehter with Foursquare’s POI dataset. It is available in the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" repository on GitHub. The style to use is","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles\/refs\/heads\/main\/style.json"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The neat thing about this style is that it only uses PMTiles vector sources. PMTiles can be hosted with a relatively simple file server (or file hosting service) instead of a more complex specialized tile server.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"pmtiles-demo.png"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"mod